@60="Shapechange
(Alteration) 

Level: 9
Range: 0
Duration: 1 hour
Casting Time: 9
Area of Effect: The caster
Saving Throw: None 

With this spell, a wizard is able to assume the form of a powerful creature. The spellcaster becomes the creature <PRO_HESHE> wishes and has almost all of its abilities. Thus, <PRO_HESHE> can change into a mind flayer to stun <PRO_HISHER> opponents and then become an iron golem to crush <PRO_HISHER> foes. These creatures have whatever Hit Points the wizard had at the time of the shapechange. Each alteration in form requires only a second, and no system shock is incurred.

The caster may choose between these six forms:
- Iron Golem (immune to most magic and elemental damage, powerful crushing attacks, poison breath weapon).
- Mind Flayer (95% magic resistance, 50% physical damage resistance, intelligence-drain attack, psionic blast at will).
- Giant Troll (regenerates 5 hp per second, powerful claw attacks).
